laboratory_examinations.findings: 1+ (<1 per 1000X FIELD): POLYMORPHONUCLEAR LEUKOCYTES. NO MICROORGANISMS SEEN.

The liver is normal in echotexture without intra- or extra-hepatic biliary ductal dilatation. Two adjacent cysts are thinly septated cysts in the right lobe measuring at most 1.8 cm. Common bile duct is nondilated, measuring 6 cm. Numerous gallstones are seen in the gallbladder neck with wall thickening, mural edema, hyperemia and positive sonographic findings compatible with cholecystitis.
